sections.about:
Queen Hotel is an excellent choice for travelers visiting Nha Trang, offering a budget friendly environment alongside many helpful amenities designed to enhance your stay.

Close to some of Nha Trang's most popular landmarks, such as St. Joseph's Parish Church (0.5 mi) and Bac Thanh Church (1.1 mi), Queen Hotel is a great destination for tourists.

As your “home away from home,” the small hotel rooms offer air conditioning, a minibar, and a refrigerator, and getting online is easy, with free wifi available.

Guests have access to a 24 hour front desk, a concierge, and room service while staying at Queen Hotel. In addition, Queen Hotel offers free instant coffee, which will help make your Nha Trang trip additionally gratifying. And, as an added convenience, there is parking available to guests.

While in Nha Trang be sure to experience local lobster favorites at Louisiane Brewhouse, Cookbook Cafe, or Costa Seafood Restaurant.

Nha Trang is also known for some great art galleries, including Long Thanh Photo Studio, Mai Loc Photo Gallery, and Colorwaves Gallery, which are not too far from Queen Hotel.

Enjoy your stay in Nha Trang!

htmlText.htmlString:
This was the hotel I stayed the first night when the receptionist of my original hotel sent me here to stay. When I was going back home to Saigon supposedly, there were issues on my bus so I stayed another night (Last Night in Nha Trang).

The receptionists and other staffs were so nice, accommodating and have been so friendly. The rooms (since I stayed in two different rooms) were clean and well groomed. The amenities may not be that fancy but were complete. If you wanna go out, there will always be people who's going to entertain anytime in 24 hours. I feel safe and secured staying there because they will always smile and be polite talking to you. I'll definitely go back there when time comes. Thanks so much.

htmlTitle.htmlString: Stuck for the First and Last Night

htmlText.htmlString: We walked in to this hotel with out a booking and we managed to get a good deal. The staff as well were so helpful and gave us many hints and tips about the city also they helped us hiring a motor bike with a very good price. We had to extend our stay for 2 more nights but the hotel was fully booked so they moved us to another better property but with the same price. Very nice and safe place.

tipText.string: you will get a better price by walking in to this hotel than pre-booking with any website

htmlText.htmlString:
Great value for money and friendly staff. Clean room and bathroom. Very basic but price is reflective of that.

Friendly staff.. offered laundry and motorbike rentals at the best price we have seen. They also booked our bus for us to Hoi An for only 200,000 vnd.

Good location.. loud in the morning due to construction though.
